COPY ~TICam/items/TITOME08.itm~ ~override/TITOME08.itm~
  SAY NAME1 ~When to her Lute Corinna Sings~
  SAY NAME2 ~When to her Lute Corinna Sings~
  SAY DESC~When to her lute Corinna sings,
Her voice revives the leaden strings,
And doth in highest notes appear,
As any challenged echo clear;
But when she doth of mourning speak,
E'en with her sighs, the strings do break,
And as her lute doth live or die,
Led by her passion, so must I:
For when of pleasure she doth sing,
My thoughts enjoy a sudden spring,
But if she doth of sorrow speak,
E'en from my heart the strings do break.~
